## What this doesn't measure

- **Target-hardware numbers.** Targets are calibrated to {{TODO: deployment hardware}}. On laptop-class hardware, anything that fits in cache or hits an SSD will look fast. Re-run on the deployment box before claiming targets are met.

- **Realistic-scale corpus.** The smoke run uses a small corpus. To stress-test, point the bench at a larger fixture set.

- **Save / write latency.** {{TODO: if applicable, why writes aren't measured here.}}

- **Cold start.** All numbers above are warm. Cold-start latency is typically 2–5× the warm number.

- **Concurrent load.** The script is sequential. A real concurrency benchmark matters for multi-user deployments.

- **Frontend rendering.** {{TODO: if applicable.}}

