## How to extend the smoke bench

If a future change introduces a new perf-sensitive endpoint, add a measurement to the script. Keep the script under ~100 lines — if benchmarking grows real teeth, fold it into a proper harness (locust, k6, or your stack's equivalent) instead of bloating the smoke script.

---

## When to re-run

- Before tagging a release.
- After any change to: {{TODO: list of perf-sensitive files / modules}}.
- After bumping {{TODO: list of perf-sensitive deps}}.

If a number regresses by >2× without a known cause, investigate before merging. The current numbers may be a long way under target, so a 2× regression is still inside the budget — but it's a useful early-warning threshold.
